		<div class="entry-content"><div class="w592"><figure class="media photo promo" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope="" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/07/12/opinion/12rollerWeb-LN/12rollerWeb-tmagArticle.jpg" itemtype="//schema.org/ImageObject" role="group"><span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span><div class="image"><img itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/07/12/opinion/12rollerWeb-LN/12rollerWeb-tmagArticle.jpg" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/07/12/opinion/12rollerWeb-LN/12rollerWeb-tmagArticle.jpg" id="100000004575586" width="592" height="394" alt="Both the Republican and Democratic conventions were held in July. &lt;a href=&quot;//www.nytimes.com/2016/07/12/opinion/campaign-stops/make-conventions-great-again.html&quot;&gt;Related Article&lt;/a&gt;"   /><meta itemprop="height" content="394"><meta itemprop="width" content="592"></div><figcaption class="caption" itemprop="description"><span class="caption-text">Both the Republican and Democratic conventions were held in July. <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2016/07/12/opinion/campaign-stops/make-conventions-great-again.html">Related Article</a></span><span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span> Damon Winter/The New York Times</span></figcaption></figure></div>
