<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>34.</strong> Four cases of <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2016/07/30/health/zika-virus-florida-case.html">_________</a> in Miami were highly likely to have been caused by infected mosquitoes, the Florida Department of Health said on July 29 â the first documented instance of local transmission in the continental United States. Three weeks later, federal health officials advised <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2016/08/20/science/5-zika-cases-were-transmitted-in-miami-beach-florida-governor-says.html">_________</a> not to visit a 20-block stretch of Miami Beach, one of the countryâs most alluring tourist destinations. At the same time, in <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2016/07/31/health/zika-virus-puerto-rico.html">_________</a>, the epidemic is raging, and the islandâs response is in chaos.</p>
